TypeSignature.Value: .class public auto ansi serializable sealed ConsoleKey extends System.Enum

Docs.summary: Specifies the standard keys on a console.

remarks.format:
## Remarks The <xref:System.ConsoleKey> enumeration is typically used in the nfo structure, which is returned by the <xref:System.Console.ReadKey%2A?displayProperty=nameWithType> method to indicate which key on the console has been pressed.
## Examples The following example uses the <xref:System.ConsoleKey> enumeration to indicate to the user which key the user had pressed.
[!code-cpp[System.ConsoleKey#1](~/samples/snippets/cpp/VS_Snippets_CLR_System/system.ConsoleKey/cpp/consolekey.cpp#1)] [!code-csharp[System.ConsoleKey#1](~/samples/snippets/csharp/VS_Snippets_CLR_System/system.ConsoleKey/cs/ConsoleKey1.cs#1)] [!code-vb[System.ConsoleKey#1](~/samples/snippets/visualbasic/VS_Snippets_CLR_System/system.ConsoleKey/vb/ConsoleKey1.vb#1)]
